<T>__{cut to:}
<L>__{exterior ship deck san francisco harbor day}
<A>__{harry helmsley, 73, and his partner tony delgado, 68, board an enormous cruise ship, the `freedom of the seas'. harry is african american, tony is italian. he carries a large case. they pass a poster: `jazz night with harry helmsley & tony delgado'.}
<C>__{harry}
<D>__{so this time we'll hit the japs.}
<C>__{tony}
<D>__{so what?}
<C>__{harry}
<D>__{well tony, electronics are cheap there and... you could visit your boy will.}
<C>__{tony}
<D>__{afternoon ladies...}
<A>__{tony shoots a charmers smile at a couple of older single ladies on sun loungers. they smile back coyly.}
<C>__{harry}
<D>__{are you even listening to me?}
<C>__{tony}
<D>__{yes unfortunately i am harry.}
<C>__{harry}
<D>__{i heard from audrey you're a grandpa now.}
<C>__{tony}
<D>__{why don't you keep your nose out of my family. you're cramping my style.}
<C>__{harry}
<D>__{he married a japanese girl how is that the end of the world? you should at least go see him.}
<C>__{tony}
<D>__{why? do you see your boy?}
<C>__{harry}
<D>__{not as much as i'd like. dc is a long way. but at least we talk.}
<C>__{tony}
<D>__{what about?}
<C>__{harry}
<D>__{life, how short it is...}
<A>__{suddenly they're thrown off balance by a large swell that pulls the massive `freedom of the seas' away from the landing, about ten yards. the next moment, the ship slams back against the dock with an earthshaking boom.}
<C>__{tony}
<D>__{what the hell was that?}
<A>__{a murmur goes through the crowd. luckily nobody is injured.}
